1 AN ACT relating to retired certified public accountants.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 325.290 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Only an individual who has received a license to practice or qualifies for a practice
5 privilege shall be styled and known as a "certified public accountant." A certified
6 public accountant may also use the abbreviation "CPA" or "public accountant."
7 (2) Licensees granted a waiver from continuing professional education based on
8 retirement may use "certified public accountant," "public accountant," or "CPA,"
9 but shall not engage in regulated activities.
10 (3) Nothing in this section shall preclude a licensee who has been granted a
11 continuing professional education waiver based on retirement from providing the
12 following uncompensated services on a volunteer basis:
13 (a) Preparing taxes;
14 (b) Participating in a government-sponsored business-mentoring program;
15 (c) Serving on the board of directors for a nonprofit or governmental
16 organization; or
17 (d) Serving on a government-appointed advisory body.
18 (4) As prescribed by the board in accordance with administrative regulations
19 promulgated by the board, licensees applying for and renewing the continuing
20 professional education waiver based on retirement shall affirm their
21 understanding of the limited types of activities in which they may engage while on
22 the waiver and their understanding that they have a professional duty to ensure
23 that they hold the professional competencies necessary to offer these limited
24 services.
